==English==

===Etymology===
1751, from earlier term {{term|colloquy}} (a conversation), from {{etyl|la}} {{term|colloquium|lang=la}} (conference, conversation), from {{term|con-|lang=la}} (together) + {{term|loqui|lang=la}} (speak).

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈkə.ləʊ.kwil̩/}}, {{SAMPA|1=/"k@.l@U.kwil=/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{linguistics}} Denoting a manner of speaking or writing that is characteristic of [[familiar]] conversation; [[informal]].
# Of or pertaining to a [[conversation]]; [[conversational]] or [[chatty]].

